cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with unsupervised learning of anomaly detection in high-dimensional data, specifically images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and encoder networks, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for addressing the problem of contaminated data, which involves stratifying the latent space, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE) research. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on a large dataset of cell images, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
